LLL - Market Data & News
LLL - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 

L-3 Communications Holdings Inc. (LLL) traded on unusually high volume on Jul. 21, as the stock 
lost 0.62% to close at $176.62. On the day, L-3 Communications Holdings Inc. saw 1.1 million shares trade hands on 10,570 trades. 
Considering that the stock averages only a daily volume of 574,940 shares a day over the last month, this represents a pretty significant bump in volume over the norm.

Generally speaking, when a stock experiences a sudden spike in trading volume, it may be seen as a bullish signal for investors. An increase in volume means more market awareness for the 
company, potentially setting up a more meaningful move in stock price. The added volume also provides a level of support and stability for price advances.

The stock has traded between $180.73 and $132.38 over the last 52-weeks, its 50-day SMA is now $167.54, and its 200-day SMA $159.55. L-3 Communications Holdings Inc. 
has a P/B ratio of 2.91. It also has a P/E ratio of 21.6.  


L3 Technologies Inc is a provider of various communication and electronic systems and products used on military, homeland security and commercial platforms. It is also a contractor in aerospace systems, security and detection systems, and pilot training.

Headquartered in New York, NY, L-3 Communications Holdings Inc. has 38,000 employees and is currently under the leadership of CEO Michael T. Strianese.


